The intersection of two sets is the set containing all elements that are common to both sets.

Set A = {1, 3, 5}
Set B = {2, 5}

The intersection of sets A and B is the set containing the elements that are in both A and B. In this case, the number 5 is the only element that is in both sets.

Therefore, the intersection of sets A and B is {5}, which has 1 element.

So, the number of elements in the intersection of sets A and B is 1.
